President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. William J. Burns is nominated for Deputy Secretary of State. He currently serves as Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs and has held various diplomatic positions throughout his career. Robert G. Taub is nominated for Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission. He has extensive experience in postal policy and was involved in developing the 2006 Postal Accountability and Enhancement Act. Mark P. Wetjen is nominated for Commissioner of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission. He currently serves as Counsel and Senior Policy Advisor to Majority Leader Harry Reid in the U.S. Senate.